” and data for “Potanin 
<number box="[256,285,793,818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" value="85.0">85</number>
” are lacking. Pichon’s label seems to refer to Hangzhou, Zhejiang Province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,685,962]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,829,854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Schenkel, 1963" authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1963" box="[344,688,829,854]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fagei">
<emphasis box="[344,503,830,854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Xysticus fagei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schenkel" box="[513,688,829,854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" refString="Schenkel, E. (1963) Ostasiatische Spinnen aus dem Museum d'Histoire naturelle de Paris. Memoires Du Museum National D'Histoire Naturelle, 25, 1 - 481." type="journal article" year="1963">
Schenkel, 
<number box="[632,688,829,854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lessert, 1919" authorityName="Lessert" authorityYear="1919" box="[980,1233,830,854]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fagei">
<emphasis box="[980,1070,830,854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">X. fagei</emphasis>
Lessert, 
<number box="[1177,1233,830,854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</taxonomicName>
from East Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick" box="[158,323,865,890]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" refString="Platnick, N. I. (2014) The World Spider Catalog. Version 14.5. American Museum of Natural History, New York Available from: http: // research. amnh. org / entomology / spiders / catalog / index. html (accessed 28 May 2014)." type="journal article" year="2014">
Platnick 
<number box="[262,323,866,890]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Because of synonymy, and accounting for the fact that the African 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1214,866,890]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fagei">
<emphasis box="[1124,1214,866,890]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">X. fagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to another species group, which seems to have its own genus name 
<emphasis box="[801,949,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Bassanioides</emphasis>
Pocock, 
<number box="[1054,1110,902,926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" value="1903.0">1903</number>
we refrain from providing a new name for this junior synonym.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" targetBox="[245,1349,1009,1953]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1977,2031]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,339,1977,2000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">FIGURES 11–14.</emphasis>
Epigyne of 
<taxonomicName box="[466,621,1978,2000]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis box="[466,621,1978,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Xysticus davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(11–12, lectotype) and 
<taxonomicName box="[866,995,1979,2000]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[866,995,1979,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">X. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(13–14, holotype). 11, 13—ventral; 12, 14 dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
Judging from the epigyne of the 
<typeStatus box="[570,668,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">holotype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName box="[676,764,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fagei">
<emphasis box="[676,764,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">X. fagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly conspecific with 
<emphasis box="[1140,1310,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1306,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiatus">X. ephippiatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The figure of the epigyne provided by Schenkel looks very different from the epigyne of the 
<typeStatus box="[1066,1168,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
